    "Kudo et al. (2022) state that informal literature reviews (unlike systematic literature reviews) are relevant for research initiatives, especially in cases based on practice.",
    "In this study an informal literature review was adopted enriched with features of integrative or else critical literature review approach, as described in Snyder (2019).",
    "The aims of using such an approach are: i) to provide the requirements engineers with an overview of the broad scope of culture, and ii) to enhance their knowledge and comprehension of the specific topics of cultural aspects in the activities related to software requirements elicitation.",
